n object to a BinPickle file. This is a convenience wrapper\naround {class}`BinPickler`.\n\nTo save with default compression for storage or transport:\n\n```\ndump(obj, 'file.bpk')\n```\n\nTo save in a file optimized for memory-mapping:\n\n```\ndump(obj, 'file.bpk', mappable=True)\n```\n\nArgs:\n\n: obj: The object to dump.\n  file(str or pathlib.Path): The file in which to save the object.\n  mappable(bool):\n\n  > If `True`, save for memory-mapping. `codec` is ignored\n  > in this case.\n\n  codec(codecs.Codec):\n\n  : The codec to use to compress the data, when not saving for\n    memory-mapping.\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "binpickle.write._log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "binpickle.write.CKOut", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "binpickle.write.CKOut.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "base", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.CKOut.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.CKOut.flush", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Wrapper for binary output that computes checksums and sizes on the fly."]}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "align", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "codec", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler.mappable", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler.compressed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "codec", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler.dump", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler.close", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler.__enter__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler.__exit__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler._init_header", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler._encode_buffer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "buf", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "out", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler._write_buffer", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "buf", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler._write_index", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.write.BinPickler._finish_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Save an object into a binary pickle file. This is like {class}`pickle.Pickler`,\nexcept it works on file paths instead of byte streams.\n\nA BinPickler is also a context manager that closes itself when exited:\n\n```\nwith BinPickler('file.bpk') as bpk:\n    bpk.dump(obj)\n```\n\nArgs:\n: filename(str or pathlib.Path):\n\n  : The path to the file to write.\n\n  align(bool):\n\n  : If `True`, align buffers to the page size.\n\n  codec:\n\n  : The codec to use for encoding buffers. This can be anything that can be\n    passed to {func}`binpickle.codecs.make_codec`, or it can be a function\n    that takes a buffer and returns the codec to use for that buffer (to\n    use different codecs for different types or sizes of buffers).\n"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs", "documentation": ["Codecs for encoding and decoding buffers in BinPickle.\n\nThis is similar in spirit to [numcodecs], but automatically handles some cases\nsuch as splitting arrays into blocks.\n\n[numcodecs]: https://numcodecs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/\n"], "functions": [{"name": "binpickle.codecs.register", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.make_codec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "codec", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "null_as_none", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "list_is_tuple", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Resolve a codec into a BinPickle-compatible codec.\n\nArgs:\n: codec(obj):\n\n  : The codec to resolve into a codec. Can be one of:\n\n    - `None` (returns {class}`Null`)\n    - A {class}`Codec` object (returned as-is)\n    - A string (look up codec by name and return with default options)\n    - A tuple `(name, config)` (pass to {func}`get_config`)\n    - A list (wrapped in {class}`Chain`)\n    - A {class}`numcodecs.abc.Codec` (wrapped in {class}`NC` and returned)\n\nReturns:\n\n: Codec: the codec.\n"]}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.get_codec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "config", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get a codec by name and configuration (as stored in the BinPickle manifest).\n\nArgs:\n\n: name(str or None): the codec name.\n  config: the codec configuration, as returned by {meth}`Codec.config`.\n\nReturns:\n\n: Codec: the configured codec.\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "binpickle.codecs._log", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.CODECS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.Null", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.GZ", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.Blosc", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.NC", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "binpickle.codecs.blosc", "xref": {"fqname": "binpickle.codecs..blosc", "project": null}}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.Chain", "xref": {"fqname": "binpickle.codecs.chain.Chain", "project": null}}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.Codec", "xref": {"fqname": "binpickle.codecs._base.Codec", "project": null}}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.gz", "xref": {"fqname": "binpickle.codecs..gz", "project": null}}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.null", "xref": {"fqname": "binpickle.codecs..null", "project": null}}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.numcodecs", "xref": {"fqname": "binpickle.codecs..numcodecs", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "binpickle.codecs.blosc", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "binpickle.codecs.blosc._split_blocks", "asynchronous": false, "params":